    "attributes": {
        "action": "Supply electric heating pads, free of means testing, to pensioners",
        "additional_details": "Used on an armchair heat can penetrate around loose clothing, and can be trapped under a fleecy rug, creating personal warmth in cold rooms. Free issue to all of pension age would make this a classless measure.\r\n \r\nWe do not live in times of ordinary economic stringency, when cynics might feel patronised by legislators who live in warm rooms. We believe this would be a welcome reaction to the specific circumstances which have caused energy price.",
        "background": "Electric heating pads consume a fraction of the energy of heaters, and can give great relief in a variety of physical ailments. As the cost of energy has soared, we believe the Government should fund the supply of these heating pads to all pensioners.",
